
[1]inkhorn

   INK'HORN, n. [ink and horn; horns being formerly used for holding ink.]

   1. A small vessel used to hold ink on a writing table or desk, or for
   carrying it about the person. Inkhorns are made of horn, glass or
   stone.

   2. A portable case for the instruments of writing.
